A number of people including a baby are believed to be trapped inside a building that has caught alight on Pixley Kaseme street previously known as the West Street in the Durban CBD, KwaZulu-Natal. Firefighters as well as paramedics are currently on scene trying to extinguish the blaze. Traffic has also been severely affected. Emer-G-Med spokesperson Kyle van Reenen says the airforce is on standby. Van Reenen says, “Smoke can be seen billowing out of the building whilst fire fighters are busy with a high angle rescue system reports at the scene are unconfirmed at this stage but it is believed that people including a baby are still trapped inside. This is a developing story and updates will follow.” Fire at a building in the Durban CBD https://t.co/PB6jjmhAEU #ArriveAlive #BuildingFire @KZN_EMS @robz_mckenzie @BurnshieldZA pic.twitter.com/rMLj5d4GCD — Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) January 21, 2022  Smoke Inhalation and Safety – How Dangerous is Smoke Inhalation and How do we Treat it? https://t.co/5ESFNgkTVp #ArriveAlive #SmokeInhalation @BurnshieldZA @robz_mckenzie pic.twitter.com/9923SmJmM9 — Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) January 21, 2022  Durban – Dr Pixley Ka Seme Street: #FIRE at China Mall – local area being cordened off pic.twitter.com/juzwuR0AG6 — Rob Beezy (@TrafficSA) January 21, 2022 